<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1527.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">MacMurray</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The loan negotiations with the five-power group have reached deadlock,
                            Minister for Foreign Affairs having last night definitely informed the
                            representatives of banks’ interests that the Government will not give
                            option for the currency loan, which they demand as a condition to their
                            granting the loan of £8,000,000 which the Chinese Government requires
                            for the purpose of discharging short-term obligations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>